An Act authorizing reserved capacity billing in the town of Norfolk.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Section 4 of chapter 354 of the acts of 2022 is hereby amended by inserting
2 after the “said chapter 83” the following words:-
3 “, or this act”
4 SECTION 2. Section 6 of said chapter 354 is hereby amended by adding the following at
5 the end thereof:-
6 “In addition, the select board of the town of Norfolk exercising the powers of a sewer
7 commission may elect to assess and collect annual charges to all customers with reserve capacity
8 for the Norfolk wastewater treatment plant on a pro rata basis, based upon such allocation of
9 capacity, not whether a property is connected to a common sewer system or its actual use. The
10 town shall have all collection remedies for such charges as it would for any rate or charge under
11 sixteen A to sixteen F, inclusive of chapter 83.”
1 of 2

12 SECTION 3. Said chapter 354 is hereby amended by inserting the following new
13 section:-
14 “SECTION 9A. A property owner may enter into an agreement to sell or transfer its
15 allocation of capacity to another parcel of land located within the town center wastewater service
16 area, subject to the approval of the select board exercising the powers of a sewer commission.”
